    Let <fr:tex>S=P^t</fr:tex> (the topological space consisting of a single point).
    We see that, for a sheaf <fr:tex>F^\bullet </fr:tex> on <fr:tex>X_\bullet </fr:tex>, the <fr:tex>\Gamma (X_n,F^n)</fr:tex> are the components of a cosimplicial set <fr:tex>\Gamma ^\bullet (X_\bullet ,F^\bullet )</fr:tex>.
    The functor <fr:tex>\Gamma </fr:tex> (of global sections) is the functor

    <fr:tree
